            <p>
              To make generic medicines available to the population, the Department of Pharmaceuticals, Government of
              India launched the Jan Aushadhi Scheme (JAS) (medicine for the masses) in 2008. Under the scheme, Jan
              Aushadhi generic drug stores were opened across the country to provide low-cost generic medicines to the
              population.
